caption: This was one of my favorite restaurants in St. Louis when I lived there for grad school.  When PokeDoke first opened, I had never heard of poke and was skeptical of fish in the Midwest, but a friend and I tried it and I they had me hook, line, and sinker.  The octopus is a great non-standard protein option and they have a wide variety of great toppings.  The dumpling and wonton sides are also great.  I have tried poke subsequently in many other cities and PokeDoke is still my #1.  One of the things I miss most about St. Louis!
Very nice.  Big bowl and tasty.
Fresh and very good! Friendly staff too
Great food and great staff!
open face sushi shop
You know how when you don't want something to end? Yeah that's how I felt!
This place reminds me of all the amazing Pokebowl places in San Diego.  The Salmon and Tuna taste great and the veg to rice ratio is perfect. Thank you for an amazing meal!
Place an order on Uber Eat “Twice”, and never get my drink
I always spend a little extra for the special add-ons for the build your own poke bowl just because in my opinion it really is worth the money. It's literally just sushi in a bowl 🥰🍣

Just found a new favorite lunch spot!🙌🏽 I recently just moved back to St. Louis from Chicago after 15 years and whenever I would come back to visit, I always felt like I couldn't find any of my favorite foods. Today, I have officially found THE BEST poke bowl I've EVER had anywhere! I ordered the Reg. Build Your Own Bowl, Shrimp Chips and Bubble Tea (Green Tea w/Boba - yes, it was Matcha Green Tea😏). After building my bowl, it came out to about $15 (Reg $13) and I was hoping 🙏🏽it was worth it because this meal was waaay more than I would usually spend on lunch. When I say the bowl was packed out, so fresh, accurate and delicious?!😋🍲 I was struggling to finish it and I have a pretty healthy appetite. Of course you don't really want to save food like this for later so I did eventually finish it but I was beyond satisfied w/the taste, the freshness, the portion and the ease of ordering online. I've never had Shrimp Chips but I quickly realized these suckers are potentially addictive especially w/some Spicy Mayo (don't judge me😒). The Bubble Tea was also really good and refreshing. I loved that the cup was perfectly sealed considering the pandemic. All in all, if you love sushi/fresh fish and you're in the CWE, go to PokeDoke for a healthy, fresh, satisfying lunch/dinner! You WILL NOT be sorry!!
KK and Alex were awesome! So friendly. My Volcano Bowl was onoclious.

Pokedoke is hands-down my favorite current restaurant in St. Louis. The food is delicious, and you honestly will not find a better poke place in the entire region. All of the food is fresh, the sauces are tasty, and they also have very good wings. On top of it all, they have the kindest, friendliest, most welcoming employees I've ever seen at a restaurant. I'm a regular and KK, Ashley, and Will (others too, but especially these three) have all remembered my name and greet me with a smile. I can't wait for the pandemic to end so I can do more in-restaurant dining!
Good good bit of a wait.

So this was my first time visiting and I must say it was absolutely amazing! I visit St. Louis frequently and decided to try something new. Ronnie, KayKay and Ashley helped me every step of the way from recommendations to their personal favorites. I will most definitely be stopping here again! Thank you for the awesome customer service and new experience!

This is my absolute favorite poke in St Louis The food is absolutely outstanding and I recommend it to anybody and everybody. You all are outstanding and I will be back numerous times thank you so much guys

I really like the experience there. I’m not asking for anything perfect, but paying extra and getting less than can be pretty frustrating, especially considering the pricing. Also, forgot my avocado which was an extra $2 :(. Every person in my (six person ) family (all who have preferences) enjoyed PokeDoke! Delectable fish, lovely seasonings, and perfectly portioned. The  regular size (with rice, or half rice/salad) was filling for the adults and teens in our family. The younger kids had a small (non spicy)dish and loved eel sauce with mango, pineapple, cucumber, and carrots with their choices of protein scoops. Our family of six will have to make this a special occasion treat, given limited finances (and adding avocado seemed very overpriced). However, the cost was appropriate given the high quality of each dish.  Additionally, we ordered curbside during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the employees were terrific: dressed carefully with masks and gloves, distanced appropriately, while remaining positive verbally and nonverbally. I was impressed with their detail to preventative directives, while also practicing hospitality during a challenging time.

This was my first experience and Kay Kay walked me through every step over the phone I had to call her back a couple times and she was really patient. I placed my order and she called me right back to mack sure that I I was coming at the suggested time so my fiod would be hot. When I got there I couldn't find a spot so Ashley ran it out to me and kept a safe distance. They were truly professional during this tough time, and made my experience super pleasant. I will be back!!

As we all know there is only carry out and delivery. We had to pick up my fiance's last check from Tom's and decide to grab lunch whole we were out. We saw this place and began to look at the menu that was posted on the glass. Then decided it looked great and headed in. The manager told us they were open but we could jot have our dog inside. We said no problem we would just decide what we wanted and then come back inside. He actually came out to us and took our order. He made some amazing recommendations as well. When I say the service was great it was great and the food is even better. Tha k you for allowing us to have a great first time experience. We hope to come back again.

PokeDoke is a great place to grab lunch or dinner. Great atmosphere and amazing service. KK and Ronnie working behind the counter gave my friends and I exceptional service with a smile. I will definitely come back. I could eat here every day.

I was directed by one of the employees on the phone I had to contact postmates to fix the issue, however after submitting my concern through the website I was offered less than half the amount I spent on the order itself. The poke bowl is what I always get and I'm never disappointed. I'm usually not a very healthy chooser but when it comes to this, I can't resist because of the really good combination of fish, veggies and sauce, that make it so delicious.

First time today at PokeDoke and everything was great! Super friendly staff, fresh ingredients, fun atmosphere. Definitely found a new lunch spot! We’ll be back!
Poke Doke is so delicious! I could eat here everyday.
Great!

What a great trip!! Its a little spot with only a few tables but when the weather gets better there are more tables outside. I was immediately greeted upon entry. One girl was helping another customer and the other was cashing someone else out. So a gentleman came from the back. They don't have a kid's size but he immediately offered an additional bowl so I could split the bowl between my daughter and myself.We got a large noodle bowl with spicy tuna, ahi tuna, shrimp and octopus medium spicy. He passed us off to the first young lady who had a great attitude. Additional toppings of green onions, avocado, masago, seaweed salad, and crab topped with spicy mayo and eel sauce. Then she passed us off to the last young lady who was also pleasant and helpful. The bowl was yummy, noodles are now my favorite base. The seafood options had a great taste and texture. My only not so great point was the Thai Boba Tea. The boba has a great taste and texture but the tea was pretty bland and not as creamy as i'm use to. But we will be back it was a great experience.

First time trying poke and oh man! If you're a sashimi and/or sushi lover you'd love this! Just a bowl of goodness. I had to get ahi tuna, salmon, spicy tuna, and a whole fried soft shell crab! Super yummu. Great for vegans/vegetarians if you get the Tofu protein option.
Great, healthy and cheap. What else can you ask for?
This place is awesome! A bit on the expensive side, but quality food nonetheless

Hi Pokedoke  Your poke is fantastic, and made even better with KK and Ashley’s attention to detail, service oriented and super friendly attitude! They are pretty amazing and I hope you appreciate them as much as we do!
Fresh poke bowl, lots of topping options. Service is friendly and quick.
Very yummy! Quality fish and delicious toppings! It was $15 for a small poke bowl and drink which was the perfect amount of food for me :)

I have been to PokeDoke twice within the past monthand plan to visit again in the very near future. Their staff are warm, especially the owner. The ingredients are always fresh and super tasty. The first time I went I had suggestions from the staff on things to add and my dish turned out super delicious! The second time I was more prepared and equally satisfied. If you love all things seafood, I recommend the Ahi Tuna, Spicy Tuna, Squid, and Shrimp. Just thinking about all of this makes me drool!! I think next time I will mix up my add-ins a little bit more. I also recommend adding masago, spicy mayo, eel sauce and some sesame seeds! If you’re considering going to this place, go now!

I Love Poke Doke , I Eat It About 2 Times A Week . Great Staff , Clean Restaurant , &  I Really Enjoyed My Time Here . Tangray And Kay Kay Are Both Two Wonderful People I Will Be Back Soon . Thanks For The Great Service !

I had an excellent experience at PokeDoke in CWE. The food was delicious and servers went above the call of duty to ensure I was enjoying my meal. If Kay Kay and Tangray are working, know that you are in good hands! 5/5 would recommend.

Unique and tasty. Can't find anything like this in St. Louis. If you like sushi you'll like their bowls. Very customizable, and very friendly staff. Webiste isn't always up and running. Often very crowded at lunch. Wish they opened up an hour earlier to deal with rush.

This is a pretty good place. It is usually crowded at lunch time so prepare. I don't  think there is much benefit to ordering ahead except you get to skip the line, but they make your food when you get there so it's not super quick. They do have chicken now which is great! You can also try bubble tea here too if interested.
Fresh and flavorful. Had the spicy tuna sushi rice bowl with seaweed salad, mango, siracha and spicy Thai sauce. It was delicious and filling!
Good, good food. Very friendly staff. EAT HERE!

This used to be my favorite poké place in St. Louis, but quality has really gone downhill in the last few months. I mean, this place was totally comparable to the poké I tried all over Hawai’i and I loved it. But ivr noticed recently that some of the fish tastes like it’s been sitting out for maybe a bit too long (the salmon and tuna), they don’t have the little fried garlic slivers anymore and done of the other classic toppings, and they skimp on portions & tell you it’s an extra charge to get the same amount of ingredients that they used to put in your bowl. That being said, the spicy tuna and drizzle selections are the saving graces here. Otherwise, the competitor poké places (and yes, there are a few in STL now!) aren’t too far of a drive.
Very enjoyable Poke bowl. Will be back. If you haven't tried Poke as a "build it yourself bowl", you are missing out.

Wow, it’s like subway but WAY BETTER and for poke. You build your own poke bowl and it is so good. The service is awesome and I love bringing people here since it’s so customizable! We don’t have many places like this in STL, but honestly I think this is the best one of the few.

Great spot for a delicious quick bite.

AMAZING all around. I was ordering lunch for my company with a larger order (~12 folks) and was worried about how complicated it might be, but I wanted to support a newer local STL business. I called and asked if doing a lunch order was possible, and Andrew and the whole team were so on top of everything. Everyone was super helpful and patient, and the logistics were explained perfectly. The food arrived early, the deliveryperson was just the best, and the food orders were even neatly labeled by name. I can't remember the last time I had such a perfectly flawless ordering experience. I'm actually getting a little emotional thinking about how stress-free this whole experience was. And, of course, most importantly, the food was on point. I'm so happy that poke is getting the love it deserves here, and PokeDoke does it so well. The value you get for the quantity and quality of a poke bowl is excellent, and there's also such a great range of toppings to choose from. (If you've never tried octopus, go for it. Also, seaweed salad as a topping is a must.) Do yourself a favor and next time you're in the CWE, stop by PokeDoke.
